product: Fabtec Waterproof and Heat Resistant Metallic Silver With Black Piping Mirror Antenna Pocket Car Body Cover Compatible wit...
title:
5.0 out of 5 stars
Liked it, Recommending
body:
I like this one, built quality, material, look and feel all superb, specially the inner lining, I like it very much, it may protect from small stone hits scratches also you know what kids do while playing. I'm always very concerned about the paint protection, dusts etc so cover is my 1st priority and always use covers after wash even when it stays in my locked garage. My old OEM cover which I got with the new car delivery 10 years back does its job excellent so far but became older so wanted to replace it since long time but didnt find one with good reviews or branded. However the older one was kind of parachute material, very light and thin which was not waterproof but if you pack the large cover it get into a small bag, very easy to carry anddont take space in boot. It was cost 1.5k 10 years back so in that respect this one is worthful at this price, I must say much betterer. However there have other good too with window side chain opening etc.But it looks bulky, it will take space into the boot after pack and maybe harder to pack/fold. My car is 2013 Verna and the cover isnt 100% perfect fit/aligned at the mirror pockets. Also no pocket for longer antenna, so had to remove it. Overall it coverup from top to bottom, no size issue and the elastics at the edges below hold it lock perfectly with good strength so it wont fly with mid wind flow.Most sad part is no carrying bag came with it. I always carry cover in the boot so if it get wet and dirty in rain I've to arrange something for it. Lets see how user friendly it is and how long it goes. Even cheap covers dont get damaged easily but the main thing is the elastics belts, once it get loosen even covers get worse in some high wind areas like near sea beaches etc. Low quality elastics damages quickly by heat and water.I always wanted a good protective cover but no time to go to market and check so took a chance with it looking at its details, reviews, rating and I'm really happy with it after covering the car first day. I will update after some use, road trips and experience of different weather.
Read more
